        <details class="why fade">
          <summary>
            <span class="why-title">Why I do this work</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="why-body">
            <p>Local shops and businesses have so much appeal that has yet to reach people. Even with great products and services, when the funnel across Instagram, ads, LINE and the website is not in place, inquiries and bookings slip away — and opportunities are lost.</p>
            <p>In my previous role I was seconded to Meta, supporting marketing for advertisers and ad agencies. What struck me there was the sheer gap in digital know-how: new tools and insights reach big-city companies and agencies quickly, while local shops and SMEs rarely even hear about the options they could be using.</p>
            <p>An ad is not finished when it runs. It only works once you design where viewers go next — and how that leads to inquiries, bookings and visits. Today, based in Otaru/Zenibako, I combine Meta ads, Instagram, LINE official accounts and AI to build funnels that carry a business's appeal to the people who need it.</p>
            <p>As populations shrink, the power to be chosen within a limited market will only matter more. I want local businesses to deliver their appeal naturally — by putting marketing and technology into a form they can actually use.</p>
            <div class="why-sign" aria-hidden="true"><img src="/logo.png?v=20260707-1519" alt="" width="46" height="46" loading="lazy" /></div>
